info.name: gb-api-v11
info.description:
## About collection

The semi-official GameBanana API v11 documentation.

## About GameBanana

[GameBanana](https://gamebanana.com/) is the game modding community established in 2001. [Learn more.](https://gamebanana.com/wikis/1917)

Authenticated users can submit, download, like, subscribe to etc. game modifications (**mods**) and/or mod-related content (e.g. blogs, concepts, news etc.)

## Basic terms and concepts

For simplicity sake, anything a user submits to GameBanana is called a `submission`.

Submissions are divided up into `sections` (e.g. skins, scripts, tools etc.)

## Collection guidelines

### Folders

Folder name must:

- Start with a noun
- Be short and descriptive
- Have a description

### Requests

Request name must:

- Start with "\[Auth\]" if it requires authentication
- Start with the step number (e.g. "1.") if it is a part of the sequence

Request description must:

- Describe response contents

Request examples must showcase:

- HTTP 2xx
- HTTP 4xx (if any)

### Path variables

Path variables must:

- (Key) Be written in snake_case
- (Value) Contain a valid example
- (Description) Follow the format: \[data type\]. \[description\]

### Query variables

Query variables must:

- (Key) Be written in gb_case (see below)
- (Value) Contain a valid example
- (Description) Follow the format: \[Required / Optional\]. \[data type\]. \[description\]

### gb_case

e.g.: _csvProperties

- underscore
- data type
- variable name in Pascal Case

## APIs

### Pagination

To paginate through APIs that return collections get `_aMetadata._bIsComplete`. If its value is `true`, there is another page to request.

query.description:
Required. Enter the search query.
Case insensitive.

Allowed values: string of 2 characters or more.

Which 'page' of results to get.

Allowed values: greater than 1.

Default value: 1

Number of results per page.

Allowed values: 1 through 50.

Default value: 20

Narrow down the search to a specific section.

Allowed values: App, Article, Bug, Blog, Club, Contest, Concept, Event, Game, Idea, Initiative, Jam, Mod, Model, Member, News, Poll, Project, Question, Review, Request, Script, Sound, Spray, Studio, Thread, Tool, Tutorial, Wiki, Wip.

How to sort results.

Allowed values: best_match, popularity, date, udate

Default value: best_match

best_match == Relevance
popularity == Popularity
date == Newest
udate == Updated

Comma-separated list of search fields.

Allowed values: name, description, article, attribs, studio, owner, credits

Default value: name,description,article,attribs,studio,owner,credits

name == Name
description == Description
article == Blurb/Readme
attribs == Tags
studio == Studio
owner == Submitter
credits == Credits
Narrow down the search to a specific Game's ID.

request.description: This endpoint returns a list of search results.

response.name: 200 Success

Well, after I downloaded the map and played it, I noticed some issues.

First: I can't believe that I played it with 4 frames :'0


Second: you have to increase the \"max viewable distance\" from map settings, this will make the map viewable from far spots.


Third: I noticed so many random cuts on the brushes, I wonder why you cut the map like this (or it's a dcompiled map?


Fourth: I think you built your map inside a big sky box, I advice you not to do that cuz it cause so many problems, you didn't fitted the walls with the ground, that's why I noticed it.


Fifth: fit the crates (boxes) texture and the ladders too.


Sixth: I suggest to reduce the water waves value.


Finally, I suggest for you to learn more about mapping in order to improve your skills, you can join the Gamebanana discord server or any other Modding server.
Also I suggest for you TWHL.info
Good Luck!!

"_aPost": { "_idRow": 10989910, "_tsDateAdded": 1690189202, "_sText": "

I played this map before in on e of the ZE Mod servers, and these are the points I noticed.

First: the start area (spawn base) is empty and poor of details, also some other places in the map looks empty.


Second: fit these two edges brushes with the top one.


Third: the boxes are poorly positioned, some of them are based on space, you can fix them manually or remove the bad ones.


Fourth: increase the \"max viewable distance\" cuz this affect the map a lot.


Finally: at the end of the map, the door texture is not fitted together with the barrier texture


The map is amazing, I hope this suggestions will help you improving your map.

First: the boxes in the sewers are poorly constructed and positioned, some of them went through the wall and some of them are based on space, you can fix them manually or remove the bad ones.


Second: also some of the lights are poorly constructed and positioned.

Finally: I liked this place here, players will stay here listening to this song and they'll forget about the escape xd...



I hope this'll help you improving your map.

The map idea is amazing, here are some suggestions to improve your map.

First: the spawn area looks empty and poor of details, you can add more details that fit the map theme for better looking.


Second: This truck in base is floating...


Third: You merged these two brushes together, you have to separate them.


Fourth: look at this water, fix it man...


Fifth: Right there, you have to add a wall or something similar, cuz this look with the sky is ugly, it also shows what's behind it...


Sixth: fit these two wall brushes with the ground.


Seventh: You can just put it in a regular position...


Finally: you have to increase the \"max viewable distance\"


I hope this'll help you improving your map :)
